article.description: Tayler Hill scored 16 of her 25 points in the second half and Ohio State (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) beat Charlotte 88-58 on Monday.
article.headline: Tayler Hill dominates in second half as Ohio State romps
article.linkText: Ohio State routs Charlotte as Hill shines with 25
article.story:
COLUMBUS, Ohio --  Tayler Hill scored 16 of her 25 points in the second half and Ohio State (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) beat Charlotte 88-58 on Monday.

Samantha Prahalis had 19 points and reserve forward Darryce Moore finished with 10 for the Buckeyes (11-0), who have won 22 of 23 dating to last season.

Hillary Sigmon had 14 points and Gabby Tyler scored 13 for the 49ers (5-5), who have lost five straight. It was Charlotte's first game since Dec. 7.

The Buckeyes showed little signs of fatigue from a red-eye flight Saturday night after their 77-75 win at California. They jumped out to a 44-14 lead.
